headline: Why PepsiCo's $1.95 Billion Bet on Poppi Makes the Stock an Attractive Buy
summary: PepsiCo (NASDAQ: PEP) is a company with more than 50 consecutive annual dividend increases under its belt.  It requires having a strong business model that gets executed well in both good times and bad.  PepsiCo's recently announced purchase of Poppi for $1.95 billion is an example of the company's strong business model being executed well during bad times.
